TDistribution - Class in com.numericalmethod.suanshu.stats.distribution.univariate
Student's t distribution is the probability distribution of t, where x̄ - μ t = ------------ s / sqrt(N) x̄ is the sample mean; μ is the population mean; s is the square root of the sample variance; N is the sample size; The importance of the Student's distribution is when (as in nearly all practical statistical work) the population standard deviation is unknown and has to be estimated from the data.
